						               													<description>Reclaim is a flip-and-write game where players will be drawing polyominos on their board and drawing triangles within certain terrains of already placed shapes to pay the cost of the new shapes.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Once a shape has been entirely filled with such triangles, the triangles within that polyomino are shaded in.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;After 10 rounds, an initial scoring happens, where players earn points based on the number of castles connected by paths of hollow triangles.  After a few more rounds, where the costs of placing a piece have doubled, players again score for connecting castles with hollow triangles but also the largest rectangle of shaded triangles (and castles). The player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
